{"id":295269550,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"3 years, 7 months","timestamp":1579360269,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"68 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/295269550/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"12.7 MB","code":"# Definition for singly-linked list.\n# class ListNode:\n#     def __init__(self, x):\n#         self.val = x\n#         self.next = None\n\nclass Solution:\n    def addTwoNumbers(self, l1: ListNode, l2: ListNode) -> ListNode:\n        \n        carry, sentinel = 0, ListNode(-1)\n        res = sentinel\n        \n        while l1 or l2:\n            x1 = l1.val if l1 else 0\n            x2 = l2.val if l2 else 0\n            carry, summ = (x1 + x2 + carry) // 10, (x1 + x2 + carry) % 10\n            res.next = ListNode(summ)\n            res = res.next\n            l1 = l1.next if l1 else l1\n            l2 = l2.next if l2 else l2\n        \n        res.next = ListNode(carry) if carry else None\n        return sentinel.next","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
